Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}. Zest and half the @lime{1/2}. Slice the @firm tofu{280}(sliced widthways into 2 thick 'steaks' per person). Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(stalks and all).

== Noodle Dressing ==

Make the dressing for the noodles by mixing the @ginger puree{1/2}, garlic, @olive oil{1}, @sugar{1}, @soy sauce{25}(half of the total) together in a #small bowl{}. Squeeze in the juice from the lime. Stir to combine then set to one side.

== Coleslaw Dressing ==

Make the dressing for the coleslaw by mixing the @rice vinegar{15} and lime zest together in a #larger bowl{}.

== Tofu and BBQ Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{1%drizzle} in a #large frying pan{} over medium-high heat. Once hot, lay the tofu slices into the pan and cook until golden, ~{4-5%minutes} on each side. Adjust the heat if necessary.

Meanwhile, make the BBQ sauce by mixing the @BBQ sauce{32}, @sriracha sauce{1} and remaining @soy sauce{25}(remaining half) together in another small bowl.

Once the tofu is golden, turn off the heat and carefully pour in the BBQ sauce. Turn the tofu over in the sauce to evenly coat.

== Noodles ==

In the meantime, pour the boiling water from your #kettle{} into a #large saucepan{} with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and bring back to the boil.

Cook the @egg noodle nests{2} for ~{4%minutes}. Drain in a #sieve{}. Return to the pan off the heat and pour in the dressing for the noodles. Sprinkle over half the @sesame seeds{15}. Toss to combine.

== To Serve ==

Sprinkle the remaining @sesame seeds{15} all over the tofu. Serve the noodles onto plates and pop the tofu (and all the BBQ sauce!) on top.

Pop the @coleslaw mix{120} on the side. Sprinkle over the remaining coriander. Tuck In!

> Looking for a tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our BBQ Tofu with Noodles and Slaw in just 20 minutes for a balanced and tasty dinnertime.